  "text": "According to this hypothesis, firms possessing intangible resources would use a direct export mode when entering a new market. As discussed above, these firms can reduce the potential for value erosion while also better assimilating information and knowledge from international markets. In contrast, firms with lower levels of intangible resources are not concerned about losing them. In addition, export intermediaries can also obtain information and knowledge that can improve a firm's exports [CITATION_1] .",
